{"id":570971,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthur_Lehning","text":"Paul Arthur M\u00FCller-Lehning (23 October 1899 \u2013 1 January 2000) was a Dutch writer, historian and anarchist. He was born in Utrecht. He was known for French translations of Mikhail Bakunin works. In 1992, he won the Gouden Ganzenveer, and in 1999, the P. C. Hooft Award.\nLehning died on 1 January 2000 in Lys-Saint-Georges, Indre, France. He was 100.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Dutch_people","surface_form":"Dutch","offset":68},{"uri":"Historian","surface_form":"historian","offset":82},{"uri":"Anarchist","surface_form":"anarchist","offset":96},{"uri":"Utrecht_(city)","surface_form":"Utrecht","offset":122},{"uri":"French_language","surface_form":"French","offset":148},{"uri":"Translation","surface_form":"translation","offset":155},{"uri":"Mikhail_Bakunin","surface_form":"Mikhail Bakunin","offset":171},{"uri":"Gouden_Ganzenveer","surface_form":"Gouden Ganzenveer","offset":214},{"uri":"P._C._Hooft_Award","surface_form":"P. C. Hooft Award","offset":250},{"uri":"Lys-Saint-Georges","surface_form":"Lys-Saint-Georges","offset":303},{"uri":"Indre_(department)","surface_form":"Indre","offset":322},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"France","offset":329},{"uri":"Centenarian","surface_form":"100","offset":344}]}